# 8. 交わる音

Saki: (We're gonna write the best song ever...)
Saki: (Ichi said that she'd turn my feelings into music.)
Saki: (To make sure Leo/need's debut single turns out amazing...)
Saki: (And I don't want to let her down!)
Saki: Ichi, I've come up with a rough melody!
Ichika: Okay, I'll listen to it now.
Ichika: Yeah, I like it...
Ichika: What you said was all there. It let me know that everything is going to be okay, and how we can all move forward together.
Saki: Really?! Thank goodness...
Ichika: *Nod* But...
Saki: Oh, what's up?!
Ichika: What if you took this part of the chorus and added it to the beginning of the song?
Saki: Huh?
Ichika: The melody for the chorus is really compelling, so I think it'd leave a nice impression if I sang right from the beginning...
Ichika: This song's about telling the listener they'll be able to move forward despite whatever is bothering them, so I feel like that'd be a good way for this song to start off.
Ichika: Then, you could gradually add more instruments to show the listener that they're not alone. That they'll be able to move forward together.
Ichika: Like we did with our band...
Saki: Oh...
Ichika: What do you think?
Saki: Yeah, you're right... Thanks, Ichi!
Saki: Then, we'll add the chorus to the beginning, and start with just us on keyboard and vocals...
Ichika: Okay, sounds good.
Ichika: So, um... Are we increasing the tempo towards the end of the chorus?
Saki: Yeah! That'll make it feel like we're running towards our goal together!
Ichika: Then, once we have every instrument involved, we could throw in a break to signal the start of the next part. How does that sound...?
Ichika: If we start playing again with just the right timing, it should provide the listener with a nice sense of togetherness.
Saki: Oh, I really like that idea...!
Saki: In that case, the following verse should try to maintain that momentum while telling the next part of the story.
Ichika: How do you want to do that?
Saki: I guess this part will be about pain or doubt... But with the sense that you need to start moving forward.
Ichika: Then, we might want to keep it a bit subdued like it already is...
Saki: Really?
Ichika: Yeah. This verse really hits home when I think about everything we went through...
Ichika: I can almost feel this melody wrapping its arms around me when I look back on what happened...
Saki: Oh...
Ichika: I know. What if we placed more of an emphasis on moving forward one step at a time?
Saki: One step at a time...?
Saki: Oh, we could throw in some triplets.
Saki: We could even have Shiho sing for this part, and Hona here!
Ichika: Yeah! Then it'd feel like we're each taking the next step!
Saki: Hehe! Alright, let's do that! Next, we have...
Saki: (This is the opposite of earlier. We can't stop coming up with good ideas now...)
Saki: (Is this because Ichi decided to do what Miku and the others did? She really understands how I feel now...)
Saki: (Which means...)
Saki: (We can do it now.)
Saki: (We have to succeed...!)
Saki: (Ichi, Miku and everyone are giving me all the help they can!)
Saki: (I have to make this the best song ever!)
Saki: It's done...!
Ichika: It finally is...!
Ichika: Your message about moving forward despite any pain or doubt is so clear...
Ichika: Which makes me really glad...
Saki: Yeah...! And I couldn't have done it without you, Ichi. Thanks for all your help!
Ichika: No, I didn't do anything...
Ichika: We have Miku and the others to thank for this.
Ichika: Because Miku and MEIKO... Everyone in SEKAI helped make this song a reality.
Saki: Yeah...
Saki: Hehe. This is so cool.
Saki: We first started our band so that we could play Miku songs together, and we really owe her and the others a lot.
Saki: Now, on top of that, they helped us produce an amazing debut single...
Saki: Which sorta means we never would've been able to get this far without our VIRTUAL SINGER friends.
Ichika: Saki...
Ichika: I agree completely...
Saki: Right?! Oh...!
Saki: Hey, you've been posting Miku versions of our songs online, right...?
Ichika: Huh? Yeah, I have...
Saki: Then, can you post this one too?
Saki: I want lots and lots of people to hear it. Also, I wanna hear what it sounds like when Miku and the others sing it...
Saki: They made this song possible, so I want to give it the respect it deserves!
Ichika: Saki...
Ichika: Yeah, you're right...!
Saki: Then, let's ask Mr. Shindo about this when we have him listen to it!
Ichika: Okay. However, there is a real possibility that we'll be told this song isn't good enough...
Saki: No way! I mean, this is our best song yet♪
Saki: Shiho and Hona also need to listen to it!
Ichika: Right!
Saki: Oh, also...
Saki: Let's make a song that properly reflects how we both feel someday, okay...?
Ichika: What...?
Saki: We went with my feeling this time, right?
Saki: But I wanna make a song about the both of us someday. Even if we can't agree on everything...
Ichika: Alright, let's pinky swear...
Ichika: Someday, we're going to write a song about us!
Saki: Yeah!
Shindo: Interesting...
Shindo: I was expecting you two to come up with a song where both of your styles and personalities would be there at the forefront...
Shindo: That being said, this is still a remarkable song.
Saki & Ichika: ...!
Shindo: Within this kindness... This empathy I'm feeling... There's a subtle but strangely powerful sound. It's like I'm being told that I'm not alone...
Shindo: You two did an excellent job making those work together. I take it you lead in writing it, Ms. Tenma, with Ms. Hoshino as more of an arranger...?
Saki: Y-Yes, that's right... We actually tried to do what you said just now at first, Mr. Shindo, but we couldn't get our feelings to really mesh...
Shindo: No, I'm beyond impressed that you were able to come up with this in such a short amount of time...
Shindo: Well done.
Shindo: It doesn't matter how things transpired. You two worked hard to make this happen, and I believe this is a good representation of what Leo/need's music is going to sound like.
Saki: Does that mean...?!
Shindo: Yes, let's go with this song. I'm sure Mr. Shimizu is also going to enjoy hearing this.
Shindo: And above all else... I've got a feeling that this is going to hit home with a lot of people.
Ichika: ...!
Saki: Th-Thank you very much!
Honami: That's wonderful to hear...! Thank you both for all your hard work!
Shiho: It's pretty incredible how you were able to come up with something this good so fast.
Saki: Hehe♪ I have Ichi and our “seniors” to thank.
Shiho: Huh?
Ichika: Miku and the others gave us some advice.
Shiho: Ah, I see.
Saki: Oh, that reminds me. Mr. Shindo, there's something we'd like to ask you...!
Shindo: Hm? Yes?
Ichika: We were hoping that we could make a VIRTUAL SINGER version of this song to post online...
Shindo: Huh?
Saki: It's just... We think that it'll help give this song more reach!
Saki: Would that be okay...?
Shindo: I see. A VIRTUAL SINGER version...
Shindo: I like it. Why not...?
Saki: Really?!
Shindo: Yes, as long as you post it after the official Leo/need version has been released. That way, people will know which is the original.
Shindo: It'll be a nice way to advertise your band.
Shindo: We can discuss when you'll be able to post it at a later date.
Saki: Woohoo! Thank you very much!
Saki: Hehe. I want lots and lots of people to hear it.
Shindo: They will. Very soon.
Shindo: However, you'll need to actually record it first. I'll be there for that, so let's all do our best to do this song justice.
Ichika: Record it...!
Saki: I-It really feels like we're pros now!
Honami: I'm a little nervous...
Shindo: You'll get used to it in no time. Things will go smoothly as long as you relax and play the way you normally do.
Saki: O-Okay...!
Shiho: He just told you to relax.
Saki: Haha. Sorry!
Shiho: But still... I don't blame you for feeling nervous or anxious. After all, this song means a lot to the both of you.
Shiho: Also, it is an amazing song...
Shiho: So, thank you both...
Honami: I'm looking forward to playing it as a band.
Saki: Me too...!
Woman: *Sigh* Seriously, how are they running this late? I'm so bored...
Ichika's Voice: <...——♪ ——♪ ——♪>
Woman: Huh? Whose song is this?
Woman: I kinda like it...
Female High Schooler: Hey, did you get a chance to listen to that song?
Female High Schooler: Yeah, it's really good. I feel so encouraged by it...
Female High Schooler: They even made a VIRTUAL SINGER version, which is also really amazing...
Male High Schooler: You've been listening to that song basically on loop lately.
Male High Schooler: Yeah, I find it really soothing for some reason. It helps put my mind at ease, and gives me a nice boost of energy.
Male High Schooler: You should give it a listen. I'll send you the link now.
Social Media Posts: <You gotta listen to this song!> <You haven't heard? Everyone's been talking about it!>
Social Media Posts: <This song motivates me to try harder.> <Miku sounds so awesome!>
Social Media Posts: <What's this band called again?>
Social Media Posts: <Leo/need!>
